
[1]neutralize

   NEUTRALIZE, v.t.

   1. To render neutral; to reduce to a state of indifference between
   different parties or opinions.

   2. In chimistry, to destroy or render inert or imperceptible the
   peculiar properties of a body by combining it with a different
   substance. Thus to neutralize acids and alkalies, is to combine them in
   such proportions that the compound will no exhibit the qualities of
   either. This is called a neutral salt.

   3. To destroy the peculiar properties or opposite dispositions of
   parties or other things, or reduce them to a state of indifference or
   inactivity; as, to neutralize parties in government; to neutralize
   opposition.

   The benefits of universities- neutralized by moral evils.

   A cloud of counter citations that neutralize each other.
